The only things that could cause issues:
ScenarioWhat happensVideo has no audio trackAPI returns error Could not extract audioUnsupported format (not mp4/avi/mov/mkv)API rejects it immediatelyVideo is corruptedAPI returns error Could not read video framesFile bigger than ~500MBWill be very slow but still work

For a normal 3MB mp4 educational video — no issues at all. Your Flutter app will get back a clean response like:
json{
  "success": true,
  "status": "approved",
  "message": "Your video has been uploaded successfully."
